Visualization Understanding of count of state wise Shipments:¶

State wise California has highest sales:

States like Texas ,New York ,etc. are active in business.

Few states like North Dakota,Wyoming and West Virgina have less or no sales at all. To generate more profit we have to increase car sales in Texas and New York where we have potential cuatomers.

To keep the profit margins the percentage of discount should be less than 25%.¶

Bussiness Understanding:¶

1.Higher number of buyers are from New York and California.

2.Most customers buy 2 or 3 quantity only.

3.Max discount give is 0 to 20%.

4.Segments wise sales are almost in every region.

5.There is no correlation between profit and Discount.

6.Profit and sales are maximum in customer segments and minimum in home office segments.

7.Profits and sales are max in west region and minimum in south region.

Weak Areas Where You Can Work To Make More Profit.¶

1.We should limit the sales of furniture and increase that of office supplies and technology as it is generating very less profit as compared to its sales.

2.In the sub-categories we are facing huge loss on tables son that should be minimized.

3.The sales and profit in Southern and Central regiobn are less so we should give morw incentives like discount in order to increase sales,hence profit will increase.

4.After the highest sales in California we have high value of potential customers in Texas and New York so we should concentrate more on these states to increase our sales and profit.

5.We have highest purchases in consumer segment biut we should also concentrate on corporate and home office segments to increase our sales and profit.

6.Few states like North Dakorta ,Wyoming and West Virgilina have less or no sales at all so we also need to focus on these states.

7.**The percentage of discount offered should not be more than 25%,otherwise loss is faced.

Main Focous Should Be On The Following Things:¶

1.Need to reduce costs.

2.Need to increase productivity.

3..Need to increse efficient product.

4.Need to give extra effort in segment area.
